TIMING-4#1 Critical Warning
Invalid primary clock redefinition on a clock tree  
Invalid clock redefinition on a clock tree. The primary clock u_clk_hdmi/inst/clk_in1 is defined downstream of clock Clk_100MHz and overrides its insertion delay and/or waveform definition
Related violations: <none>

TIMING-6#1 Critical Warning
No common primary clock between related clocks  
The clocks Clk_100MHz and clk_out1_clk_wiz_hdmi are related (timed together) but they have no common primary clock. The design could fail in hardware. To find a timing path between these clocks, run the following command: report_timing -from [get_clocks Clk_100MHz] -to [get_clocks clk_out1_clk_wiz_hdmi]
Related violations: <none>

TIMING-7#1 Critical Warning
No common node between related clocks  
The clocks Clk_100MHz and clk_out1_clk_wiz_hdmi are related (timed together) but they have no common node. The design could fail in hardware. To find a timing path between these clocks, run the following command: report_timing -from [get_clocks Clk_100MHz] -to [get_clocks clk_out1_clk_wiz_hdmi]
Related violations: <none>

TIMING-27#1 Critical Warning
Invalid primary clock on hierarchical pin  
A primary clock u_clk_hdmi/inst/clk_in1 is created on an inappropriate internal pin u_clk_hdmi/inst/clk_in1. It is not recommended to create a primary clock on a hierarchical pin when its driver pin has a fanout connected to multiple clock pins
Related violations: <none>

LUTAR-1#1 Warning
LUT drives async reset alert  
LUT cell u_hdmi/i_wrap_i_1, with 2 or more inputs, drives asynchronous preset/clear pin(s) u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_0/i_ODDRE_N/RST, u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_0/i_ODDRE_P/RST,
u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_1/i_ODDRE_N/RST, u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_1/i_ODDRE_P/RST,
u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_2/i_ODDRE_N/RST, u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_2/i_ODDRE_P/RST,
u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_3/i_ODDRE_N/RST, u_hdmi/i_wrap/TMDS_3/i_ODDRE_P/RST. The LUT may glitch and trigger an unexpected reset, even if it is a properly timed path.
Related violations: <none>

